{"parentUuid":"3cf98486-8850-4984-bc24-fd9a43072a09","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ae758cc42afc8818b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Xr6ioVbzBBubjZzazR4CA2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018RufpJGHLfeLqdJB1waa7X","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"distillation 7B 8B student model gains accuracy fine-tuning traces"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3646,"cache_read_input_tokens":12352,"output_tokens":150,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3646},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":150,"cache_read_input_tokens":12352,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3646,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3646,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcFqLsqJhipDGYSi6MZsE","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"42c258ca-f6d4-4ef1-9139-c0ec3f11dfb1","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:21.610Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"3cf98486-8850-4984-bc24-fd9a43072a09","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"ae758cc42afc8818b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WvoPaxzDfJ9u9q6JdJu7TS","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"LLM routing cascade cost quality tradeoff RouteLLM FrugalGPT savings\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"RouteLLM: Learning to Route LLMs with Preference Data\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2406.18665\"},{\"title\":\"ConsRoute:Consistency-Aware Adaptive Query Routing for Cloud-Edge-Device Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.21237\"},{\"title\":\"xRouter: Training Cost-Aware LLMs Orchestration System via Reinforcement Learning\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2510.08439v1\"},{\"title\":\"LLM Routing and Model Cascades: How to Cut AI Costs Without Sacrificing Quality - TianPan.co\",\"url\":\"https://tianpan.co/blog/2025-11-03-llm-routing-model-cascades\"},{\"title\":\"MixLLM: Dynamic Routing in Mixed Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.18482\"},{\"title\":\"Rerouting LLM Routers\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2501.01818\"},{\"title\":\"LDP: An Identity-Aware Protocol for Multi-Agent LLM Systems\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.08852\"},{\"title\":\"Dynamic Model Routing and Cascading for Efficient LLM Inference: A Survey\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.04445\"},{\"title\":\"A Unified Approach to Routing and Cascading for LLMs\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2410.10347v3\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 LLM Routing Techniques\",\"url\":\"https://www.getmaxim.ai/articles/top-5-llm-routing-techniques/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about LLM routing, cascading strategies, and the cost-quality tradeoff:\n\n## Cost-Quality Tradeoff\n\nResearch using RouteLLM shows that with proper routing, you can maintain 95% of frontier model quality while routing 85% of queries to cheaper models, achieving cost reductions of 45–85% depending on your workload. On benchmarks like GSM8K (grade school math problems), routing can achieve 95% of GPT-4's performance while using GPT-4 for only 14% of queries.\n\n## RouteLLM Approach\n\nLLM routing offers an effective solution by first processing each user query through a router, which then determines the most suitable LLM to handle the query. The router can direct simpler queries to smaller models and more complex ones to larger models. RouteLLM introduced four distinct routing strategies, including similarity-weighted ranking, matrix factorization, and supervised and prompting classification.\n\n## FrugalGPT Cascading Approach\n\nFrugalGPT follows a cascading approach, sequentially querying LLMs until a reliable response is obtained. FrugalGPT arranges multiple LLMs into a cost-ordered chain and uses a DistilBERT classifier to predict the correctness of each intermediate answer; if the predicted correctness is low, the router escalates to the next, more expensive model.\n\n## Key Difference\n\nCascading methods that rely on multiple LLM queries can increase latency. In contrast, RouteLLM routes each query to a single LLM, addressing latency constraints.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"bf4ff2d4-0327-4f90-b9b4-134359ce6094","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:29.770Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"LLM routing cascade cost quality tradeoff RouteLLM FrugalGPT savings","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01MYiGdi8Bu4jA2cfKRgvpje","content":[{"title":"RouteLLM: Learning to Route LLMs with Preference Data","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2406.18665"},{"title":"ConsRoute:Consistency-Aware Adaptive Query Routing for Cloud-Edge-Device Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.21237"},{"title":"xRouter: Training Cost-Aware LLMs Orchestration System via Reinforcement Learning","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2510.08439v1"},{"title":"LLM Routing and Model Cascades: How to Cut AI Costs Without Sacrificing Quality - TianPan.co","url":"https://tianpan.co/blog/2025-11-03-llm-routing-model-cascades"},{"title":"MixLLM: Dynamic Routing in Mixed Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.18482"},{"title":"Rerouting LLM Routers","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2501.01818"},{"title":"LDP: An Identity-Aware Protocol for Multi-Agent LLM Systems","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.08852"},{"title":"Dynamic Model Routing and Cascading for Efficient LLM Inference: A Survey","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.04445"},{"title":"A Unified Approach to Routing and Cascading for LLMs","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2410.10347v3"},{"title":"Top 5 LLM Routing Techniques","url":"https://www.getmaxim.ai/articles/top-5-llm-routing-techniques/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about LLM routing, cascading strategies, and the cost-quality tradeoff:\n\n## Cost-Quality Tradeoff\n\nResearch using RouteLLM shows that with proper routing, you can maintain 95% of frontier model quality while routing 85% of queries to cheaper models, achieving cost reductions of 45–85% depending on your workload. On benchmarks like GSM8K (grade school math problems), routing can achieve 95% of GPT-4's performance while using GPT-4 for only 14% of queries.\n\n## RouteLLM Approach\n\nLLM routing offers an effective solution by first processing each user query through a router, which then determines the most suitable LLM to handle the query. The router can direct simpler queries to smaller models and more complex ones to larger models. RouteLLM introduced four distinct routing strategies, including similarity-weighted ranking, matrix factorization, and supervised and prompting classification.\n\n## FrugalGPT Cascading Approach\n\nFrugalGPT follows a cascading approach, sequentially querying LLMs until a reliable response is obtained. FrugalGPT arranges multiple LLMs into a cost-ordered chain and uses a DistilBERT classifier to predict the correctness of each intermediate answer; if the predicted correctness is low, the router escalates to the next, more expensive model.\n\n## Key Difference\n\nCascading methods that rely on multiple LLM queries can increase latency. In contrast, RouteLLM routes each query to a single LLM, addressing latency constraints."],"durationSeconds":8.434892624999396,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3cf98486-8850-4984-bc24-fd9a43072a09","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"42c258ca-f6d4-4ef1-9139-c0ec3f11dfb1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"ae758cc42afc8818b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018RufpJGHLfeLqdJB1waa7X","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"distillation 7B 8B student model gains accuracy fine-tuning traces\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"What Is Model Distillation? Definition & FutureAGI (2026)\",\"url\":\"https://futureagi.com/glossary/model-distillation/\"},{\"title\":\"Trace-of-Thought Prompting: Investigating Prompt-Based Knowledge   Distillation Through Question Decomposition\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.20946\"},{\"title\":\"DeepSeek-R1 Distilled Models Overview\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/deepseek-r1-distilled-models\"},{\"title\":\"Model Distillation on GPU Cloud: Train an 8B Student from a 70B Teacher | Spheron Blog\",\"url\":\"https://www.spheron.network/blog/model-distillation-gpu-cloud-7b-student-70b-teacher/\"},{\"title\":\"Supervised and distillation fine-tuning for open models | Gemini Enterprise Agent Platform | Google Cloud Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/models/tuning/open-model-tuning\"},{\"title\":\"Distilling Llama3.1 8B into 1B in torchtune – PyTorch\",\"url\":\"https://pytorch.org/blog/llama-into-torchtune/\"},{\"title\":\"Enhancing Knowledge Distillation for LLMs with Response-Priming   Prompting\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2412.17846\"},{\"title\":\"Distillation vs Fine-Tuning: What's the Difference? — distil labs\",\"url\":\"https://www.distillabs.ai/learn/distillation-vs-fine-tuning/\"},{\"title\":\"Where Did This Sentence Come From? Tracing Provenance in LLM Reasoning Distillation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.20908\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive search results on model distillation with 7B and 8B student models, fine-tuning, and performance gains. Here's what the search reveals:\n\n## Knowledge Distillation Performance Gains\n\nDistilled 7B-13B students typically retain 70–85% of their frontier teacher's MMLU-Pro accuracy and 50–70% of GPQA Diamond.\n\nOn general-purpose benchmarks (MMLU, HellaSwag), a well-distilled 8B student typically scores 3-8 percentage points below its 70B teacher, though on narrow domain tasks where you distilled with task-specific data, the gap often closes to under 2%.\n\n## Fine-tuning and Teacher Traces\n\nA team distills Claude Sonnet 4.6 behavior into a Llama 4 8B student via supervised fine-tuning on 50K teacher-generated traces. Additionally, Table-R1-SFT, a 7B-parameter Qwen or Llama3.1, distilled from 33k DeepSeek-R1 traces, achieves dramatic EM/accuracy gains on multiple tabular benchmarks in-domain and OOD.\n\n## Teacher Sentence Correlation with Accuracy\n\nRecent research shows that across different models (DeepSeek-R1-0528-Qwen3-8B and DeepSeek-Distill-Qwen-7B), Teacher Sentence tends to be assigned higher probabilities to correct answers, since the teacher model achieves higher performance and the student model benefits from producing outputs more aligned with the teacher.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"da08ed32-234b-4198-8ee7-66a8f7803682","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:14:30.036Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"distillation 7B 8B student model gains accuracy fine-tuning traces","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01HndYNoDDyiiEyLe1vZqJrd","content":[{"title":"What Is Model Distillation? Definition & FutureAGI (2026)","url":"https://futureagi.com/glossary/model-distillation/"},{"title":"Trace-of-Thought Prompting: Investigating Prompt-Based Knowledge   Distillation Through Question Decomposition","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.20946"},{"title":"DeepSeek-R1 Distilled Models Overview","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/deepseek-r1-distilled-models"},{"title":"Model Distillation on GPU Cloud: Train an 8B Student from a 70B Teacher | Spheron Blog","url":"https://www.spheron.network/blog/model-distillation-gpu-cloud-7b-student-70b-teacher/"},{"title":"Supervised and distillation fine-tuning for open models | Gemini Enterprise Agent Platform | Google Cloud Documentation","url":"https://docs.cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/models/tuning/open-model-tuning"},{"title":"Distilling Llama3.1 8B into 1B in torchtune – PyTorch","url":"https://pytorch.org/blog/llama-into-torchtune/"},{"title":"Enhancing Knowledge Distillation for LLMs with Response-Priming   Prompting","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2412.17846"},{"title":"Distillation vs Fine-Tuning: What's the Difference? — distil labs","url":"https://www.distillabs.ai/learn/distillation-vs-fine-tuning/"},{"title":"Where Did This Sentence Come From? Tracing Provenance in LLM Reasoning Distillation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.20908"}]},"I found comprehensive search results on model distillation with 7B and 8B student models, fine-tuning, and performance gains. Here's what the search reveals:\n\n## Knowledge Distillation Performance Gains\n\nDistilled 7B-13B students typically retain 70–85% of their frontier teacher's MMLU-Pro accuracy and 50–70% of GPQA Diamond.\n\nOn general-purpose benchmarks (MMLU, HellaSwag), a well-distilled 8B student typically scores 3-8 percentage points below its 70B teacher, though on narrow domain tasks where you distilled with task-specific data, the gap often closes to under 2%.\n\n## Fine-tuning and Teacher Traces\n\nA team distills Claude Sonnet 4.6 behavior into a Llama 4 8B student via supervised fine-tuning on 50K teacher-generated traces. Additionally, Table-R1-SFT, a 7B-parameter Qwen or Llama3.1, distilled from 33k DeepSeek-R1 traces, achieves dramatic EM/accuracy gains on multiple tabular benchmarks in-domain and OOD.\n\n## Teacher Sentence Correlation with Accuracy\n\nRecent research shows that across different models (DeepSeek-R1-0528-Qwen3-8B and DeepSeek-Distill-Qwen-7B), Teacher Sentence tends to be assigned higher probabilities to correct answers, since the teacher model achieves higher performance and the student model benefits from producing outputs more aligned with the teacher."],"durationSeconds":8.23852950000018,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"42c258ca-f6d4-4ef1-9139-c0ec3f11dfb1","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
